   <talk_paragraph index="n249_saint_guard-1" image="" itemindex="" portrait_left="" portrait_right="" center_image="">
      <talk_answer link_index="n249_saint_guard-1-a" mid="9" select_type="0"><![CDATA[<html>Well, that's right. Why did you want to see me?</html>]]></talk_answer>
      <talk_question mid="7"><![CDATA[<html>$Royal Guard Roy$<BR>
It's been a long time. I heard you're busy nowadays.</html>]]></talk_question>
   </talk_paragraph>
   <talk_paragraph index="n249_saint_guard-1-a" image="" itemindex="" portrait_left="" portrait_right="" center_image="">
      <talk_answer link_index="n249_saint_guard-1-b" mid="11" select_type="0"><![CDATA[<html>Really?</html>]]></talk_answer>
      <talk_question mid="10"><![CDATA[<html>$Royal Guard Roy$<BR>
I've recently heard the news that the <FONT color=#a94407>Battlefield</FONT> is calling for the best of the best heroes.</html>]]></talk_question>
   </talk_paragraph>
   <talk_paragraph index="n249_saint_guard-1-b" image="" itemindex="" portrait_left="" portrait_right="" center_image="">
      <talk_answer link_index="n249_saint_guard-1-c" mid="13" select_type="0"><![CDATA[<html>(...)</html>]]></talk_answer>
      <talk_question mid="12"><![CDATA[<html>$Royal Guard Roy$<BR>
I guess you really were busy. Were you <FONT color=#a94407>saving the world</FONT> or something?</html>]]></talk_question>
   </talk_paragraph>
   <talk_paragraph index="n249_saint_guard-1-c" image="" itemindex="" portrait_left="" portrait_right="" center_image="">
      <talk_answer link_index="n249_saint_guard-1-d" mid="15" select_type="0"><![CDATA[<html>What kind of rules?</html>]]></talk_answer>
      <talk_question mid="14"><![CDATA[<html>$Royal Guard Roy$<BR>
You must have your own reasons. Anyway, what was I about to tell you? Right, the new battlefield! This battlefield has <FONT color=#a94407>different rules</FONT> compared to the previous one.</html>]]></talk_question>
   </talk_paragraph>
   <talk_paragraph index="n249_saint_guard-1-d" image="" itemindex="" portrait_left="" portrait_right="" center_image="">
      <talk_answer link_index="n249_saint_guard-1-e" mid="17" select_type="0"><![CDATA[<html>Sounds fun. Please go on.</html>]]></talk_answer>
      <talk_question mid="16"><![CDATA[<html>$Royal Guard Roy$<BR>
Rather than <FONT color=#a94407>Hero vs. Hero (PvP)</FONT>, it will be more of a <FONT color=#a94407>Hero vs. Monster (PvE)</FONT> style.<BR>
Does that sound interesting to you?</html>]]></talk_question>
   </talk_paragraph>
   <talk_paragraph index="n249_saint_guard-1-e" image="" itemindex="" portrait_left="" portrait_right="" center_image="">
      <talk_answer link_index="n249_saint_guard-1-f" mid="19" select_type="0"><![CDATA[<html>Huh? Then what's the difference between the new battlefield and normal dungeons and nests...?</html>]]></talk_answer>
      <talk_question mid="18"><![CDATA[<html>$Royal Guard Roy$<BR>
It is not only about killing enemies or destroying major props. In this battlefield, you'll find numerous monsters and your victory will depend on the <FONT color=#a82424>points attained</FONT> from killing those monsters.</html>]]></talk_question>
   </talk_paragraph>
   <talk_paragraph index="n249_saint_guard-1-f" image="" itemindex="" portrait_left="" portrait_right="" center_image="">
      <talk_answer link_index="n249_saint_guard-1-g" mid="21" select_type="0"><![CDATA[<html>I see.</html>]]></talk_answer>
      <talk_question mid="20"><![CDATA[<html>$Royal Guard Roy$<BR>
Well, it's a competition between two sides. You can kill the opponent team's player and steal some of the point the opponent had gained by killing monsters.</html>]]></talk_question>
   </talk_paragraph>
   <talk_paragraph index="n249_saint_guard-1-g" image="" itemindex="" portrait_left="" portrait_right="" center_image="">
      <talk_answer link_index="n249_saint_guard-1-h" mid="23" select_type="0"><![CDATA[<html>Then how do I enter?</html>]]></talk_answer>
      <talk_question mid="22"><![CDATA[<html>$Royal Guard Roy$<BR>
You would have to strategise whether to kill monsters, steal points from enemies who have killed the monsters, or to protect allies who are killing the monsters. I'm sure it will be an interesting battle even for heroes who are not keen on PvP. </html>]]></talk_question>
   </talk_paragraph>
   <talk_paragraph index="n249_saint_guard-1-h" image="" itemindex="" portrait_left="" portrait_right="" center_image="">
      <talk_answer link_index="n249_saint_guard-1-i" mid="25" select_type="0"><![CDATA[<html>I see...</html>]]></talk_answer>
      <talk_question mid="24"><![CDATA[<html>$Royal Guard Roy$<BR>
You don't have to get a team beforehand because you have to enter the battlefield through matching. Press [<FONT color=#a82424>N</FONT>] to open the main menu and click [<FONT color=#a82424>Battlefield</FONT>] at the top and select [<FONT color=#a82424>Request Matching</FONT>]. Easy, isn't it?<BR>
 </html>]]></talk_question>
   </talk_paragraph>
   <talk_paragraph index="n249_saint_guard-1-i" image="" itemindex="" portrait_left="" portrait_right="" center_image="">
      <talk_answer link_index="n249_saint_guard-1-j" mid="27" select_type="0"><![CDATA[<html>Okay.</html>]]></talk_answer>
      <talk_question mid="26"><![CDATA[<html>$Royal Guard Roy$<BR>
Please take note that you can still talk to NPCs or use the store during matching, but you can't leave town or use the Cash Shop.</html>]]></talk_question>
   </talk_paragraph>
   <talk_paragraph index="n249_saint_guard-1-j" image="" itemindex="" portrait_left="" portrait_right="" center_image="">
      <talk_answer link_index="n249_saint_guard-1-k" mid="29" select_type="0"><![CDATA[<html>Make it short please.</html>]]></talk_answer>
      <talk_question mid="28"><![CDATA[<html>$Royal Guard Roy$<BR>
To summarise the rules for [<FONT color=#a82424>Rumble Mode</FONT>]...</html>]]></talk_question>
   </talk_paragraph>
   <talk_paragraph index="n249_saint_guard-1-k" image="" itemindex="" portrait_left="" portrait_right="" center_image="">
      <talk_answer link_index="n249_saint_guard-1-l" mid="31" select_type="0"><![CDATA[<html>Not short enough!!</html>]]></talk_answer>
      <talk_question mid="30"><![CDATA[<html>$Royal Guard Roy$<BR>
<FONT color=#7e12d2>1. Although points are attained by killing monsters, you can also kill opponents who have points to steal their points!</FONT><BR>
<FONT color=#7e12d2>2. You can enter by clicking [Battlefield] button then selecting [Request Matching].</FONT><BR>
<FONT color=#7e12d2>3. You cannot leave the town during matching.</FONT><BR>
<FONT color=#7e12d2>4. You win if you have attained enough points within the time limit or have more points than the opponent team when the time is up!</FONT><BR>
 </html>]]></talk_question>
   </talk_paragraph>
   <talk_paragraph index="n249_saint_guard-1-l" image="" itemindex="" portrait_left="" portrait_right="" center_image="">
      <talk_answer link_index="n249_saint_guard-1-m" mid="33" select_type="0"><![CDATA[<html>Okay.</html>]]></talk_answer>
      <talk_question mid="32"><![CDATA[<html>$Royal Guard Roy$<BR>
<FONT color=#2b2723>I know seeing it for yourself would be much better than hearing my long-winded explanations! I'm sure you will enjoy it even if you are not confident with PvP. You get to test how strong you are and earn rewards at the same time, how much better can it get?</FONT></html>]]></talk_question>
   </talk_paragraph>
   <talk_paragraph index="n249_saint_guard-1-m" image="" itemindex="" portrait_left="" portrait_right="" center_image="">
